File: File: Pensioners over the age of 65 can bring their IDs to enter stores between 7am and 8am. JOHANNESBURG - Pick n Pay will be prioritising elderly shoppers by opening supermarkets and hypermarkets an hour earlier every Wednesday. WATCH: WHO warns against hoarding The elderly are particularly vulnerable to the coronavirus. Pensioners over the age of 65 can bring their IDs to enter stores between 7 and 8am.   The dedicated shopping hour will give the elderly exclusive use of the store. READ: On a roll: The psychology behind toilet paper panic The move is aimed at limiting the amount of time they spend in crowded spaces. On Monday, several people in South Africa  headed to supermarkets to stock up on goods amid coronavirus fears. South Africa has 62 confirmed cases that tested positive for COVID-19.